column5: GiGi had a banner day He caught his largest pike ever he watched his daughter catch a 30 inch walleye and he watched his grandson catch a huge walleye.     The ladies caught some very very nice walleye
sorry couldn't find the originals without the titles just more photos of big fish.
Can't beat free advertising.
Alota nice pics here, especialy the Nipi. spec.  This is my first time posting, hope you enjoy.                    As you can tell Im a Bit of a trout guy. Look forward to posting a report sometime.
Look at the back on that last fish!!!  Holy crap!!!  Awesome fish man!!
WELL YOU ASKED FOR IT !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Damn does this make me look better
Interesting bunch of fish! Welcome to the board, hope to see more of you,  Cheers
Welcome, very nice fish and photos, given the background in this pic that's the last species of trout I would have expected. Hope to see more, thanks.
Beautiful pics Selfmade05.  Those brookies are spectacular!
Aren't the 'giant' brookies in some of those pics actually splake?  If not... good god.

dave524 All fish in those picks come from back lakes. Thats a bow not a steelhead and the specs are not nipi. specs although someday I will have the chance to catch some of those beauts.  BillM The three that follow the laker are 2 female splake and one male splake with a kype. The others are specs, first one was a big spring female and the last one was big kyped male which is out there putn the weight on as we speak.  Just have to learn how to catch steelhead now.

Oh ok... since you twisted my rubber arm...   here is some of my best from 2009 and 2010.  27" Walleye  20" Smallmouth bass  Nice largemouth bass caught in a storm  20.5" Smallmouth bass  42" Muskie  43" Muskie  Release shot  47" Muskie (PB... caught solo so nobody to take pic  )  Release shot  47" Muskie (tied PB from the 5 days before!)  40" Muskie... fatty!  27" Laker (PB)  25" Whitefish (PB)  24" Laker
Amazing fishin pictures Dave524 and Fisherpete!!!
Very cool man, I don't think I've ever hooked into a splake..  Steelhead are easy, you shouldn't have any problems with them   Just learn to become a weatherman and you'll be all set, lol.
Sorry, my mistake, I thought the one I quoted looked like a brown with  the spotting initially.  edit : Mike none of the pics were mine , unfortunately.
My Biggest fish ever, and I still have her.
You sir are a legend in my eyes. May I please ask when your taking me fishing?
Your are right the first Fish is a brown. The second fish or first spec is a spec not a splake.
decent muskie    decent laker    decent walter    decent pike
Terry.....nice fish but you have WAY too much time on your hands
Obviously we have a very different perception of what "Decent" is...  You're just making us squirm ain't ya?!

AWESOME GUYS    Nice collection of big ones.... Congrats to all   :clapping: Here's some of my PB's from last year  5lbs 6oz Largie    32" snake    My first whitie    19" walleye    18" x 12" speckle    Leechman
31 inch, 10 lb walleye

Why does it always gotta be about size to y'all ......  Nice Simcoe laker   A pair of simcoe tank whities    10lb kawartha eye   next is a pair of very respectable kawartha skis       All fish returned to the water unharmed..... and the whities well they were released in a pan of hot oil!
Here are a few from 2009              I enjoy the photos of  the Kids best                     This one is just too pretty not to share.

I had the opportunity to fish some different bodies of water over the past year and have put a few PB in the boat and on the bank including a 29lb Muskie and an 11lb Atlantic.  Lets see some of your big fish pics from the last year!
Hopefully there'll be several giant esox lucious for 2010 eh buddy?  Nice fishies.
My largest Pike is only 12lbs so I think I'll beat that on the first few casts! 4 more months!
Bill, you just trumped all of my fish with that brookie.  Amazing fish!
I plan on trumping that brookie with monster snakes in June!!!  lol
is that from the st.mary's river by any chance? rapids.....? lol
that second pic is in the sault eh?
Brookies are trump, 9 of brookie beats an ace of pike.  Great fish and photos everyone
Actually...One eyed jackfish and the man with the fillet knife (Cronzy) are wild.
So far my biggest this year was this Northern Pike and my Lake  trout. And my most prized catch done last August was this PB Largemouth...as everybody here has seen a thousand times          MTBF

Here's a few from the big pond last season -  Biggest brown ever for me which tipped the scales @ 19# -    Then next weekend caught my biggest king (male) which tilted the scale @ 33.70# -     Cheers, G.
BillM...the pike and the walleye are nice, but, that Brookie.............AMAZING...they really are the most beautiful fish!!
Largemouth Bass - 9lb 6 oz   Smallmouth Bass - 6lbs 1 oz   Walleye - 10lbs 7oz
Here is one nice smallies I caught on Simcoe....6Lbs 2 oz....and a 5 1/2 pound largie.
My favorite catches:       Not a big fish but lots of fun on a 1Lb leader.
That is the ugliest 19 fisherman I have ever seen     Here is a 45lber we call Harry he likes to eat cut shad and we have caught him 3 times in the last 3 years.   Art

I love multi-species, so here's a few different fish:  Walleye   Steelhead   Jumbo Perch   King Salmon - Cha-Ching! $$$   Channel Catfish   Freshwater Drum (Sheephead)   Close-up of a 350lb Blue Marlin   Barracuda   And while I didn't catch this one, it seems a nice addition to the thread  Tuna!   Best of luck in 2010 for all you hawg hunters out there Tony
